\begin_layout Section
Discussion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:discussion"

\end_inset

[Placeholder discussion section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Key points to develop:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
 The enforcement equilibrium: Why MCCs chose alpha = 0.
 Measurement technology alone leads to enforcement (rejection of adulterated
 milk) rather than price differentiation.
 This is consistent with models of collective action problems where MCCs
 have limited incentive to invest in quality-differentiated pricing when
 they can simply enforce minimum standards.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
2.
 Why alpha > 0 does not emerge endogenously.
 Possible explanations include: coordination failures among MCCs, limited
 downstream demand for quality differentiation from processors, farmer heterogene
ity making graded pricing administratively costly, and social norms around
 uniform pricing in cooperatives.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
3.
 Policy implications.
 Making quality visible is necessary but not sufficient for creating markets
 for quality.
 Additional interventions that directly create price incentives (such as
 quality bonuses or graded pricing mandates) are needed to move from enforcement
 equilibria to quality-differentiated markets.
 This has implications for the design of quality infrastructure programs
 in developing country agricultural value chains.]
\end_layout

